 <H1>Views and Security</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>Views can be used to present necessary information (or a summary), while hiding details in underlying relation(s).
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Given ActiveSailors, but not Sailors or Reserves, we can find sailors who have a reservation, but not the bid’s of boats that have been reserved.
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>The GRANT/REVOKE commands can be used to control access to relations and views.
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Together with the ability to define views, this provides a very powerful access control mechanism. </H2>
</UL></P>
